hat performs a custom routine, such as canceling the selection operation, whenever this event occurs.  \\n  \\n When you create a GridViewSelectEventHandler delegate, you identify the method that will handle the event. To associate the event with your event handler, add an instance of the delegate to the event. The event handler is called whenever the event occurs, unless you remove the delegate. For more information about event-handler delegates, see [NIB: Events and Delegates](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/d98fd58b-fa4f-4598-8378-addf4355a115).\"\n  example:\n  - \"The following example demonstrates how to programmatically add a GridViewSelectEventHandler delegate to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.GridView.SelectedIndexChanging> event of a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.GridView> control.  \\n  \\n [!code-cs[GridViewSelectEventHandler#1](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_132_1.aspx)]\\n [!code-vb[GridViewSelectEventHandler#1](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_132_1.aspx)]  \\n  \\n The following example demonstrates how to declaratively add a GridViewSelectEventHandler delegate to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.GridView.SelectedIndexChanging> event of a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.GridView> control.  \\n  \\n [!code-cs[GridViewSelect#1](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_132_2.aspx)]\\n [!code-vb[GridViewSelect#1](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_132_2.aspx)]\"\n  syntax:\n    content: public delegate void GridViewSelectEventHandler(object sender, GridViewSelectEventArgs e);\n  inheritance:\n  - System.Delegate\n  platform:\n  - net462\nreferences:\n- uid: System.Delegate\n  isExternal: false\n  name: System.Delegate\n"}